ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes I would definitely recommend this class if interested in the anthropology of development or conservation, or even if you want to know more about Foucault, Tsing, Scott and Li.

Absolutely, if you are at all interested in development or anthropological theory, this is the woman to talk to. Take any of her classes, but this one especially for its broader treatment of core issues in the anthropological study of development..

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I will definitely be using this class for my thesis and it has put me on an entirely different path than I set out on when coming to the school.
